%8A%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%B1%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cause to become, to render, to make","tags":["ditransitive"],"examples":[{"text":"صَيَّرَتِ الْبُرُودَةُ الْمَاءَ جَلِيدًا.","english":"Coldness turned the water into ice."},{"text":"صَيَّرَ ٱلْحُلْوَ مَرِيرًا","english":"to turn sweet into bitter"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"brine","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dried and fermented river fish, fry (main ingredient of the spice paste صِحْنَاء (ṣiḥnāʔ))","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of صَارَ (ṣāra) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb","obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"nonstandard form of سَيْر (sayr, “strap; antler …”)","tags":["alt-of","nonstandard","obsolete"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Aramaic צִיר (ṣīr, “the own juice wherein fish is conserved; fish brine”). Also in Hebrew צִיר (ṣīr, “sauce, broth, gravy, brine”). In Classical Syriac instead with unemphatic anlaut: ܣܼܝܪܵܐ (sīrā) used for the sense of small dried fish in the Grecized plural ܣܼܝܪ̈ܲܣ (sīras) or ܣܼܝܪܸ̈ܣ (sīres), hence apparently identical to the “strap” word found in Arabic more usually as سَيْر (sayr) than as صَيْر (ṣayr), referring to fish so small that they would only be apprehended as a “thread”."},"ipa":["/sˤaj.ja.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n25184","headword_ar":"صَيِّرٌ","root":"Swr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Goodly in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Suwrap","text_ar":"صُورَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"form"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]; (Fr, S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaArN","text_ar":"صَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$wr","text_ar":"شور"},{"kind":"text","text":".) One says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN Say~irN $ay~irN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ صَيِّرٌ شَيِّرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, S) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aArN","text_ar":"شَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaArN","text_ar":"صَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA ubi suprà)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man goodly in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Swrp","text_ar":"صورة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"form"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aArap","text_ar":"شَارَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appearance"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apparel"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (Fr, S.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ay~irN","text_ar":"شَيِّرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$wr","text_ar":"شور"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["Fr","S"]},{"entry_id":"n25339","headword_ar":"صَيِّرٌ","root":"Syr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A grave."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, O, K. [Perhaps so called as being the ulterior abode.]) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA","text_ar":"هٰذَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Say~iru fulaAnK","text_ar":"صَيِّرُ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is the grave of such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O.)       -A2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A company"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jamaAEap","text_ar":"جَمَاعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"). (O, K.)       -A3-  See also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Swr","text_ar":"صور"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n25334","headword_ar":"صَيْرٌ","root":"Syr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see what next follows."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n25335","headword_ar":"صِيرٌ","root":"Syr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ulterior"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ultimate, latter"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"last, state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"end, conclusion, event, issue,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"result;"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing, an affair, or a case; (S, M, O, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SayorN","text_ar":"صَيْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maSiyrN","text_ar":"مَصِيرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maSiyrapN","text_ar":"مَصِيرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Say~uwrN","text_ar":"صَيُّورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fayoEuwlN","text_ar":"فَيْعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Say~uwrapN","text_ar":"صَيُّورَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b2-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"verge, brink,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"point,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of an affair, or event. (M, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaA EalaY","text_ar":"اَنَا عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiyrK mino A^amori ka*aA","text_ar":"صِيرٍ مِنْ اَمْرِ كَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I am on the verge of such an affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"event."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaA EalaY SiyrK mino HaAjatiY","text_ar":"اَنَا عَلَى صِيرٍ مِنْ حَاجَتِى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I am at the point of"},{"kind":"text","text":"[attaining]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the object of my want."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaA EalaY SiyrK mino qaDaA='i HaAjatiY","text_ar":"اَنَا عَلَى صِيرٍ مِنْ قَضَا=ءِ حَاجَتِى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I am at the point of accomplishing my want."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN EalaY Siyri A^amorK","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ عَلَى صِيرِ اَمْرٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is at the point of accomplishing an affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A water at which people stay,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abide;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, O, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiyrapN","text_ar":"صِيرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A crevice"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a door. (S, M, A, Msb, K.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano naZara fiY","text_ar":"مَنْ نَظَرَ فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Siyri baAbK fafuqiy^ato Eayonuhu fahiYa hadarN","text_ar":"صِيرِ بَابٍ فَفُقِيَتْ عَيْنُهُ فَهِىَ هَدَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Whosoever looks into the crevice of a door and has his eye put out, it is a thing for which no mulct is to be exacted"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, M:) A'Obeyd says that this is the only instance in which the word [in this sense] has been heard. (S.)       -A4-  [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condiment, made of small fish, called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiHonaAp","text_ar":"صِحْنَاة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, M, K:) or ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a condiment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SHnAp","text_ar":"صحناة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is called in Pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAhiY A=waho","text_ar":"مَاهِى ا=وَهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"jelly of salted fish"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiHonaApN","text_ar":"صِحْنَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SHnAp","text_ar":"صحناة"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small salted fish of which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SHnAp","text_ar":"صحناة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is made:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kr, M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the young ones of fish:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a coll. gen. n.:] n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) thought by IDrd to be Syriac; (TA;) by IAth, to be Pers., as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SHnAp","text_ar":"صحناة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SHn","text_ar":"صحن"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A5-  Also The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usofuf~","text_ar":"اُسْفُفّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[properly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bishop"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the Jews."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.)       -A6-  See also the next paragraph."}],"source_refs":["O","K","S","Msb","TA","M","Kr"]}]}}